<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum75/HTML/000151.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#400000"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#400000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Darrow</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">okay, PVP is fine.  People who want to Pk can, people who don't, don't.  What is the problem in this?  Pk's hate fighting those not ready for PvP?  Course, an even fight is the last place you will see a PK.<P>What is needed in the game right now is balance.  Archery has been nerfed to the extreme, axe/dagger/staff suck for the most part, even the magic ones.  Swords is the big weapon, and everyone is using it.  How bout a little balance?  Give each weapon class it's own SoLL style weapon, or up the guardian, (like the now legandary lev 106 magma golem). TO ungrade weapons would not be bad.  Axe should, for the most part be slower and hit harder than sword.  Staff should be weaken and faster, dagger even more extreme.  But right now, With SoLL, swords has one of the strongest damage weapons for the arcane lore, and one of the fastest.  It is unbalanced.  I wold like to see and axe of lost light, being slower, doing more damage, and instead of swiftkiller, getting 2 more levels of blooddrinker.  It is fair and balanced, sword is faster, axe hits harder.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Aspasia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Even Though You Felt It Nescessary To Repeat Yourself Several Times, I Was Able To Understand Your Message Quite Early. Axe Has Been One Of My Favorite Weapons For Quite Some Time.. It's Carried Over From Game To Game... It's Just An Amusing Thing To Fight With. And I Have Noticed The Unbalance In AC, Also... My Guess Is That There's Just Jut Enough Physics Modeling In The Game TO Notice Much Of A Difference.. And Just A Lack Of Thought Put Into Seperating Weapon Classes. They All Use The Same Formula To Find Your Skill, So Anybody Could Be Good With Just About Anything.. However They Gravitate Towards The Better Weapons.. And Since There's Mostly Swords Out There And They Do Some Of The Best Damage... Guess What Weapon It Is That People Favor Most? But Think Of It.. Someone With A Good Dagger Skill Should Be Able To Pummel Someone With Equal Sword Skill If Their Defence Is Up there.. But The Sword Will Win Because It's Equal In Nature To The Dagger, And There's Not Much Of A Way For The Dagger To Become More Deadly. Also With Staffs.. Wouldn't They Break If Someone Came At Them With A Big Old Lugian Axe? Come On Now.. Who Can Block That? It's Slow As All Hell And Does Some Decent Damage, But Only Because It's A Hulk Of A Thing And Easy To Program As So. So What I Propose Is That Some Thought Go Into The Weapon Systems.. Because Not Everybody Has Swords On Their Mind.. Some Of Us Like Other Things.. My Personal Fav In AC Is The "Unarmed" Weapons. Atractive And Letal If The Skill Is High... But Where Are The Special Ones? Where Are The Katars Of Lost Light? Hehe.. Oh Well.. I'll Settle For Enchanting Them Myself, I Guess</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Joe Napalm</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Interesting use of capitals...quite annoying...I applaud you. Grin.<P>I seem to recall Turbine commenting that the SoLL was a special case - pretty much because it costs more to get a sword skill than any other weapon skill. <P>The SoLL is very powerful, but you have to be able to GET one! Is its power out of whack with the risks invovled in getting one? I don't think so. You have to get the Seven Keys, survive the Dires, the HoLL, the GoLL...<P>Also - there are special weapons of all types, you just hear more about the SoLL because it is unique in it's power and only the first person to grab it can ever use it.<P>I can't help but wonder, though - if you are going to choose a particular weapon, be it for roleplaying reasons or just for style, does it really matter that there might be a sword out there that is more powerful? It's not like EVERYONE has a SoLL.<P>As a Blademaster, I realize the problems associated with being a sword-user. First of all, sword is by far the most popular weapon, so you have a LOT of competition when it comes to aquiring a decent weapon. As far as finding magical weapons, I have found more spears than anything else - I have found several axes, hammers (uses the axe skill), maces, bows, crossbows, staves, unarmed weapons of various descriptions, and daggers. <P>I have a follower who is an Axe specialist. I've provided her with at least three axes that are far superior to my own blade. All three were elemental with two or three potent enchantments... while I still use an exquisitely-crafted Ivory Tachi (I traded another nice axe for it).<P>-Jn-<p>[This message has been edited by Joe Napalm (edited October 11, 1999).]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
